GOLDEN SPREAD ELECTRIC COOPERATIVE, INC. MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF
1. Availability. Golden Spread Electric Cooperative, Inc. (Golden Spread) will make electric capacity, energy and ancillary services available under this Rate Schedule for wholesale sales to any purchaser.
2. Applicability. This Rate Schedule is applicable to all market-based sales of capacity, energy, and ancillary service by Golden Spread.
3. Rates. All sales shall be made at the rates established between Golden Spread and the purchaser.
4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established between the purchaser and Golden Spread.
5. Effective Date. This Rate Schedule shall become effective on the date specified by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Compliance with Commission Regulations
Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller’s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller’s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller’s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority
None
Seller Category
Seller is a Category 2 seller in Southwest Power Pool region and a Category 1 seller in all other regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a).
Ancillary Services
Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (SPP) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP.
Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation and Frequency Response Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generation Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, and Operating Reserve-Supplemental. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation and Frequency Response Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider’s OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.
